  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• Electron irradiation of sodium-containing glasses results in the spatial redistribution of Na ions. • Electron irradiation decreases ion exchange Ag for Na efficiency or block it. • Silver nanoparticles formation depends on the irradiation doze, and can be blocked or facilitated. • Observed effects can be used for the control of ion exchange for integrated optics fabrication.</subfield>
